So when I fix R, the number of ordered pairs (Q, S) is 11*10 = 110. But in reality, for each R, there are 11 choices for Q and 10 choices for S (since Q R and S R and Q S). So when I calculated 40 valid (Q, S) pairs for each R, that's 40 per R. Therefore, total valid triples: 12*40 = 480. Total triples: 12*11*10 = 1320. 480/1320 simplifies to 4/11.
